SIMPLE: implicit
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Implicit
<hw>Im*plic"it</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>implicitus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>implicare</ets> to entwine,
entangle, attach closely: cf. F. <ets>implicite</ets>. See
<er>Implicate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Infolded; entangled;
complicated; involved.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In his woolly fleece⟦br⟧
I cling <qex>implicit</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Tacitly comprised; fairly to be understood, though
not expressed in words; implied; <as>as, an implicit contract or
agreement</as>.</def> <rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Resting on another; trusting in the word or
authority of another, without doubt or reserve; unquestioning; complete;
<as>as, <ex>implicit</ex> confidence; <ex>implicit</ex>
obedience.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Back again to <qex>implicit</qex> faith I fall.</q>
<rj><qau>Donne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Implicit function</b></col>. <fld>(Math.)</fld> <cd>See
under <er>Function</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Implicitly</ent>⟦br⟧
